Thanks for finally fixing the mage epic graphic with models off.  However, I hope that the necromancer specter pet upgrade is simply the beginning of caster balance.  At no point, ever, should a necromancer pet outdamage a magician pet.  ESPECIALLY the mage epic pet.  The one thing magicians did best in eq has now been taken away (hopefully only temporarily).  As a refresher, mage epic is lvl 49, quads 67, procs a 143dd (spec pet procs a high damage life tap, dont recall exact number, something around 100 i believe), and sometimes casts a 167dd+stun.  Specter pet has about 2800 hp, epic pet has about 3000.  Niether pet gets hit unless soloing so the hp is not significant, especially considering that the necro pet lifetaps and therefore has &quot;more hp&quot; during a fight.<br>
